blogs.title: Reading my horses their horoscopes
blogs.body:
If you've pulled the Star card, you know you're going the right way. If you're setting goals for yourself, you'll make sure to see them through. And though rewards may still be on the horizon, the Star's presence is a nice sign that you can continue to the future on the path that you're on. Relax, allow yourself to enjoy the journey, and always keep striving.Fueled by bright energy, the Star card radiates red and orange colors. At the top, the Aquarius glyph is fully present, a testament to the Star's quest for bigger and better futures. Let its optimism fuel you forward.

Now if that doesn't describe my horse Elizabeth-Ann, then I don't know what does. She's such an aquarius!

Open your heart, Capricorn! If someone in your orbit is going through a rough patch, drop your guard and lend them a shoulder to cry on. A supportive one-on-one could make a world of difference in this person’s life, thanks to today’s compassionate moon-Neptune trine. Resist the urge to interject with unsolicited advice and just practice active listening instead. If you’re the one struggling, send out your smoke signals. A good old fashioned vent session will make you feel SO much better!

This one describes my pony Lemon-Zest to a tee! I hope he gets over whatever has been bothering him lately...
